  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3791",
  "title": "Pass in label for primary index",
  "body": "**Feature request**\r\n\r\nI'd like to give the main index a label when using a custom autocomplete widget with multiple indices. Additional indices added in the widget can have a label and I would like to be able to label the main index for output on the front end also.\r\n\r\nHere's my code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport instantsearch from 'instantsearch.js';\r\nimport { connectAutocomplete } from 'instantsearch.js/es/connectors';\r\n\r\nimport searchClient from '../../algolia/searchClient';\r\nimport { autocomplete } from '../../algolia/widgets';\r\n\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  indexName: 'destination',\r\n  searchClient,\r\n});\r\n\r\nconst customAutocomplete = connectAutocomplete(autocomplete);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  customAutocomplete({\r\n    container: document.querySelector('#my-search-box'),\r\n    indices: [\r\n      { label: 'Hotels', value: 'hotel' },\r\n    ],\r\n  }),\r\n);\r\n\r\nsearch.start();\r\n```\r\n\r\nI pass in the index \"destination\" as my main index, then add an additional index of \"hotels\" to my custom autocomplete widget. I am able to label this one but not the main \"destination\" index, and on the front end the label returns \"primary\".\r\n\r\nI didn't find any way to do this in the docs/issues/stack overflow. Apologies in advance if I've missed it.\r\n",
